This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning, specifically the use of distributed word representations to automatically extend knowledge bases. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of linear algebraic structures and singular value decomposition, which are common techniques in machine learning and data analysis, suggesting that it could also fit into categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with information retrieval and knowledge discovery, which could place it in categories such as cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
